1> In addition, shaman at higher levels seem to tend to die a lot from debuffing those uber mobs.  Our level 60 shaman dies more than any other member of the guild, bar none.  Once the mob is pulled, the shaman (at least ours) starts debuffing almost immediately to reduce damage to tanks and therefore keep our clerics from having to dump mana and get aggro.  Any resist usually equals a dead shaman (any druid will know that if you have to cast a debuff several times you WILL get aggro), which means he ends up having to med back from zero after rezz, a lot.  The running joke in the guild is that it's not an official raid till Guladan dies.<br>
<br>
On another note, although I'm sure it was not the intent of the original poster, even implying that shaman are too uber will doubtlessly get several screaming babies over to whineplay complaining that they aren't uber compared to those overpowered shaman.  Another post joked about starting something like that, but it's not really a joke.  Someone will complain becuase they just can't stand that another class might have a plus that they don't.<br>
<br>
Example:  FoH used to post spoilers on the uber equipment they got.  In particular I'm talking about the gear that dropped from the ToV boss mob (whatever it's name is).  One such item was an absolutely fantastic dagger.  Apparently, some (no doubt envious) folks starting whining about it being too good and the item reportedly ended up getting nerfed (I don't know how it was nerfed).  FoH, and now Afterlife (who recently killed the boss mob), will no longer post spoilers on the uber gear they get.  You can check out the FoH message board for more info on what happened.<br>
<br>
I'm not pointing fingers at anyone here.  I'm just saying that even planting an idea in some whiners head can have unforseen results.  A lot of folks may think I'm overreacting or comparing apples and oranges.  I don't.  Please try to refrain from saying other classes are overpowered.  As Druids, we should be sensitive to what can happen since our DoT nerf from so long ago can be attributed to others complaining about druids being able to solo too easily (I don't care if anyone says Verant just has it out for Druids and soloing, the vast majority of our nerfs were due to the complaints of other players, IMO).<br>
<br>
If I were the shaman that solo'd whatever uber mob, I wouldn't tell anyone but my guild and would request they not tell anyone else.  If that gets around enough, you will see a shaman nerf down the road.  Guaranteed.  <br>
<br>
As an earlier post said, if you have improvements for the druid class, just put forth the improvements you'd like to see.  Don't compare us to others.   Don't put any ideas in Verant's collective mind.  Don't get another class nerfed.  I really hope wizards aren't over on their board talking about how good Druids have it with PotG, Mask, Howler, etc.<br>
<br>
By the way, this is coming from someone that isn't anti-Verant.  But even though I'm not an anti-verant fanatic (no offense Scirocco), I can still see the wisdom in not pointing out possible nerf material.<br>
<br>
